items.summary: Lots of people like this place

pageInfo.description:
Serving up the best dumplings, noodles and sesame pancakes in New York City

www.vanessas.com

items.text: My girlfriend dumped me after I took her on a date here... she was a skank anyway-this place awesome!
This tiny little venue has tiny little prices for their delightful dumplings. The sesame pancakes are also great, and perfect to grab to-go on your way to picnic in the park, just a block west.
get the pork sesame pancake sandwich!
Amazing dumplings.  Pork sandwich looked super delicious too (I'm trying that next time).  You can try cutting the line by ordering at the window outside, but that's a real crapshoot.
For $5 or less, fill up on some of NYC’s greatest cheap dumplings. Try the sesame pancakes for $.50 each and get 3 pork fried buns for $1.
The pancake lady works 14 hours a day.  She is awesome.

let's be honest: the dumplings here are middling at best. skip 'em & splurge on the wontons in chili oil for $4—they're delicious! easily one of the best things you can eat in all of nyc for under $5.
Real hard to get a seat. Have one person get in line and order while the other snags a place to sit. Teamwork.
dinner for two under ten bucks and its good..wtf?
Bargain dumplings
The dumplings aren't the best in Chinatown, but their crisp, doughnut-light sesame pancakes stuffed with meat and vegetables are great.
$9 will get you two orders of chive pork fried dumplings, two orders of pork fried buns and two orders of sesame pancakes. I would highly recommend all aforementioned items. All very good. #nyceats
Get the #8 and thank me later.
Get the pancake sandwich. for 1.25 you really can't beat the price.
you can never use enough sriracha
Soo good!  Fried Pork dumplings are my favorite. I would highly recommend this place if you like Asian food. Very yummy
This awesome dumpling house will fill you up!  Get the sesame pancake and pair it with the hot and sour soup.  Yum!
Get 100 frozen dumplings! So easy and yummy to make at home
An order of pork dumplings, hot & sour soup, and sesame pancake w/veggies will cure that hangover.
You can get an ungodly amount of food for less than $6 - 3 chive and pork dumplings, 3 pork buns, 1 sesame pancake with pork. And it's pretty good.
